contextMenu.description:
Note: To disable a context menu item,
copy it to User Preferences and add the
"disabled" key. The following example will disable Download item on files:
{
  "contextMenu": [
    {
      "command": "filebrowser:download",
      "selector": ".jp-DirListing-item[data-isdir=\"false\"]",
      "disabled": true
    }
  ]
}

Context menu description:

overrides.description:
Overrides for where to show sidebar items
e.g., {"jp-debugger-sidebar": "left"}
You can also change this by right-clicking the sidebar icons.

toolbar.description:
Note: To disable a toolbar item,
copy it to User Preferences and add the
"disabled" key. The following example will disable the delimiter selector item:
{
  "toolbar": [
    {
      "name": "delimiter",
      "disabled": true
    }
  ]
}

